  {
    "client_msg_id": "55d2db7d-30e0-482b-9215-29d3f4f28d12",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Kind of. I am interested in making learning easier for children and having a more equitable world, which made me interested in Esperanto (kiun mi pli-malpli lernis) which led me to learn about Helmar Frank's research on the <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propaedeutic_value_of_Esperanto|propaedeutic value of Esperanto>, which led me to think \"gee, most people won't understand learning Esperanto as a way of learning English... wouldn't it work better to teach a language that was explicitly designed to be a path to learning English (but which secretly has much of the benefits of being an easy-to-learn interlanguage that could potentially supplant English in environments where it is rarely used in the first place)?\"",
    "user": "UD6EXQVM0",
    "ts": "1585022783.002300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
